US$686.6 million (2014)



Number of employees

3,000 (April 2015)


Website
www.crowehorwath.com


Crowe Horwath LLP is one of the largest public accounting,[dead link] consulting, and technology firms in the U.S. Crowe is an independent member of Crowe Horwath International.



Contents


1 History

1.1 Founding
1.2 Name change to Crowe Horwath


2 Services
3 Industry recognition
4 References
5 External links



History[edit]
Founding[edit]
Crowe Chizek was established in 1942 in South Bend, Ind., by Fred P. Crowe Sr. and Cletus F. Chizek. Previously, Crowe had worked in public accounting for many years and also served as the St. Joseph County auditor for eight years. Chizek was head of the accounting department at the University of Notre Dame and also worked part-time in public accounting. Following the death of Fred P.Crowe Sr. in 1952, Cletus F. Chizek reorganized the firm as Crowe, Chizek and Company and two firm personnel, M. Mendel Piser and Fred P. Crowe Jr., became partners. The first legal partnership of Crowe Chizek and Company was formulated in 1962 with six founding partners: Cletus F. Chizek, M. Mendel Piser, Fred P. Crowe Jr., Robert W. Green, Joseph A. Bauters and John J. Pairitz.[1]
Name change to Crowe Horwath[edit]
The firm changed its name to Crowe Horwath in 2008 to strengthen its alignment with Horwath International and in 2009 Horwath International changed its name to Crowe Horwath International. The new name combined the international awareness of the Horwath brand with the United States awareness of Crowe Horwath LLP (Crowe), the network’s largest member firm in the U.S.
Historically, Crowe is one of the fastest growing firms with an average annual growth rate of 17 percent over the past 40 years.[2]
Services[edit]
Audit, Tax, Advisory, Risk, and Performance.[3]
Industry recognition[edit]

The 2015 Accounting Today Top 100 Ranks Crowe in the Top 10 in the U.S.[dead link]
2015 PAR Top 100 Ranks Crowe in the Top 10 in the U.S. [4]
2015 101 National Best and Brightest Companies to Work For[5]
2016 Best Places to Work in Kentucky[6]
2016 Best Places to Work in Vermont[7]
2015 Best Places to Work in New Jersey[8]
2015 West Michigan 101 Best and Brightest Companies to Work For[9]
2015 Ohio's Best Employers[10]
2015 Atlanta's Best and Brightest Companies to Work For[11]
2015 Best Places to Work in Illinois[12]
2014 Best companies to work for in Texas[13]

